🔁 7. FULL 15-SERVICE EXECUTION PLAN

⸻

🧩 WAVE STRATEGY

⸻

🔹 Wave 0 (Preparation)
	•	Infra deployed using:
	•	Amazon EKS
	•	Amazon RDS for PostgreSQL
	•	Amazon MQ

⸻

🔹 Wave 1 (Services 1–3)

For EACH service:

Step 1: Shadow Deploy
	•	Deploy in AWS
	•	Still using ON-PREM DB + MQ

⸻

Step 2: Enable replication
	•	Postgres → RDS
	•	RabbitMQ → Federation

⸻

Step 3: Switch dependencies
	•	Update config:
	•	DB → RDS
	•	MQ → AWS MQ

⸻

Step 4: Parallel run
	•	Compare outputs

⸻

Step 5: Cutover
	•	Freeze producers
	•	Drain queues
	•	Route traffic → AWS

⸻

Step 6: Monitor

⸻

🔹 Wave 2 (Services 4–8)

Same steps but faster (pattern reuse)

⸻

🔹 Wave 3 (Critical Core Services 9–15)
	•	Longer validation window
	•	More strict reconciliation

⸻

🔄 8. ROLLBACK RUNBOOK

1. Detect issue
2. Switch DNS → ON-PREM
3. Resume ON-PREM MQ
4. Disable AWS consumers


⸻

🔐 9. DR + FAILOVER RUNBOOK

⸻

Failure Scenario

AWS failure →
Promote RDS replica →
Restart services →
Switch DNS


